description:
Collects the mini-series Ronin.

A dishonored, masterless 13th-century samurai - a ronin - is reborn into the corrupt and computerized New York City of the 21st century with one last chance for redemption. It is here, on the bleak and decaying battleground, that he will at last come face to face with the reincarnation of his former master's killer - the ancient demon Agat - settle past debts, and fight for the soul of the dying civilization.

A powerful tale of two sworn enemies and the final battle in their centuries-old war, RONIN is acclaimed writer-artist Frank Miller's breakthrough graphic novel that paved the way for the multiple award-winning Batman: The Dark Knight Returns.
name: Ronin

description:
Black Jack is a mysterious and charismatic young genius surgeon who travels the world performing amazing and impossible medical feats. Though a trained physician, he refuses to accept a medical license due to his hatred and mistrust of the medical community's hypocrisy and corruption. This leads Black Jack to occasional run-ins with the authorities, as well as from gangsters and criminals who approach him for illegal operations.Black Jack charges exorbitant fees for his services, the proceeds from which he uses to fund environmental projects and to aid victims of crime and corrupt capitalists. But because Black Jack keeps his true motives secret, his ethics are perceived as questionable and he is considered a selfish, uncaring devil. The Black Jack series is told in short stories. Each volume will contain 16-20 stories, each running approximately 20-24 pages in length.Black Jack is recognized as Osamu Tezuka's third most famous series, after Astro Boy and Kimba, the White Lion.

English translation of the Japanese manga Burakku Jakku.
name: Black Jack

description:
These are the first 2 issues from the AC Collector Classics and is titled 'Cliffhanger Comics" 1A featuring The Masked Marvel on the cover, and 2A with Don Winslow of the Coast Guard (Navy) on the cover.

Each issue features a new story featuring the Republic Serial movie character The Masked Marvel, Bob Barton. Each story features new art and not photo reprints, but illustrated stories done in the vein of the original 1943 Serial of the same name.

Both issues feature stories involving Don Winslow of the Navy, and the Western character Rocky Lane, both of whom have had their own comics from other companies.

Other issues exist but the first ones in the series are 1A and 2A.

This Masked Marvel character should not be confused with other comic book characters of the same name.
name: Cliffhanger Comics
